tags: Male characters get slammed as well
If anything it is a double standard where Dany is not supposed to be criticized at all
title: People Judge Male Characters Harshly
body: I get tired of hearing that Dany is somehow harshly judged because she is a woman.  Most fans judge male characters harshly as well.  No one, outside of a few hardcore book fans, likes Stannis.  And the first words out of most people’s mouth when it comes to Jon is to ask why the writers made him so stupid.

summary: Look...Im pretty much content with the fact that everyone i like on game of thrones is going to die in season 8...but...
body: Look…Im pretty much content with the fact that everyone i like on game of thrones is going to die in season 8…but honestly,If they make dany nissa nissa, that’ll be a disgusting way to end her story line. Like imagine all that she has been through because of men,only for her to die because of a man,a man that is supposed to be her greatest love. And yeah i know being nissa nissa is like supposed to be a big honor because her death is the only way Azor Ahai is able to forge light bringer (I say patronizing but thats me) and hence the only way the long night is ended,but nah fuck that! A badass woman,who has been through hell and back, to die as a small footnote in someone else’s heroic journey is GROSS! The ink is dry now,because the show is prettymuch done,but if its one thing I ask for is for dany’s story not to end like that.

summary: New ‘Game of Thrones’ footage shows Sansa’s first meeting with Daenerys
title: New ‘Game of Thrones’ footage shows Sansa’s first meeting with Daenerys
body:
Game of Thrones fans have been starved for months for a look at the show’s final season, and we finally got one during the 2019 Golden Globe Awards.

In a new promo for HBO’s 2019 seasons, we witness Sansa Stark’s first meeting with Daenerys Targaryen, who arrives in Winterfell on the arm of Jon Snow.

“Winterfell is yours, your grace,” says Sansa. We can only imagine how loaded those words are from one queen to another – Jon’s relationship to either notwithstanding. Also, Dany’s winter furs are fresh as hell!

Game of Thrones returns in April.

Read more: https://mashable.com/video/golden-globes-2019-game-of-thrones-season-8-preview/
